[{"question":"What was it like?","answer":"It\u0027s unlike anything I\u0027ve ever covered before.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":30,"aSentId":31},{"question":"Why do you think they did that and why him?","answer":"Well, you know, it\u0027s interesting.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":57,"aSentId":58},{"question":"When does he give his first mass and so on?","answer":"He\u0027s -- they have a schedule for him that\u0027s set out the next few days that has with him having mass tomorrow in a discreet way, and he\u0027ll start to build towards more public appearances.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":85,"aSentId":86},{"question":"How significant is that choice of name?","answer":"Totally significant.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":120,"aSentId":121},{"question":"What is the general reaction, do you think, from the cardinals who have elected this man?","answer":"Well, first of all, I think if there is a great sense of relief that they\u0027re not the Pope.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":143,"aSentId":144},{"question":"And what do you imagine his idea of reformation may be?","answer":"Well, you know, I think what we\u0027re talking about here is a man who is very much, as every one of the 115 cardinals, is an orthodox man.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":184,"aSentId":185},{"question":"Is that the kind of person, do you think, that the Catholic Church needs?","answer":"ANTORUM: He is, in my -- I would not call him a progressive conservative.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":205,"aSentId":206},{"question":"Do you think he\u0027s going to go after this?","answer":"I have no doubt that this is a man who, as you heard talk about, is very much committed to doing the right thing, to standing up for the truth and for making sure that people are held to account, and to holiness, I think, a couple of your commentators said.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":224,"aSentId":225},{"question":"Could you see yourself supporting that if he said that?","answer":"Well, I\u0027m not going to -- I\u0027m not going to make this judgment until I hear the rationale for, you know, the theological rationale and underpinning as to why that is a morally right thing to do.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":237,"aSentId":238},{"question":"And that surely in the end is a Christian answer, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Well, the most important thing is to save souls.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":250,"aSentId":251},{"question":"What is your view about changing times, changing moods amongst -- certainly young Catholics?","answer":"I don\u0027t think that we can expect from Pope Francis any move along the lines you were just suggesting.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":269,"aSentId":270},{"question":"What is your belief?","answer":"There is none that I know.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":336,"aSentId":337},{"question":"Is he going to move, do you think, on any of these key things?","answer":"I think the most important thing is his personal credibility.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":352,"aSentId":353},{"question":"But could it be a problem later in his life?","answer":"I doubt it, Piers, exactly for the reason that you\u0027re mentioning.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":376,"aSentId":377},{"question":"Are you surprised that they went for somebody of that age, or not really?","answer":"Well, age isn\u0027t measured in years as much anymore, Piers, as you know.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":396,"aSentId":397},{"question":"Mr. Speaker, how are you?","answer":"I\u0027m doing well.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":414,"aSentId":415},{"question":"What is your immediate gut reaction to this appointment of Pope Francis?","answer":"Well, I think the fact that he became Pope Francis is extraordinarily important.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":418,"aSentId":419},{"question":"Has that given him a taste, do you think of, what battles may be to come?","answer":"Look, I\u0027m going to go out on a limb for a second.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":435,"aSentId":436},{"question":"I mean, if we would just -- you know, in the middle of all of the elites\u0027 angst about their personal lives, if we could just look at it for a second and say, won\u0027t it be amazing to have a Pope who genuinely focusing, in the tradition of Saint Francis, on helping the poorest among us?","answer":"Listen, with great respect, Mr. Speaker -- we\u0027re going to take a quick break.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":450,"aSentId":451},{"question":"Have you made up with him?","answer":"I can\u0027t believe you used that word on evening television.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":515,"aSentId":516},{"question":"Were you offended by that?","answer":"I wasn\u0027t worried about me.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":519,"aSentId":520},{"question":"But are you best buddies again with Roger Ailes?","answer":"Look, I have no idea what he said to a reporter who reported all that.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":524,"aSentId":525},{"question":"But are you seriously going to do this?","answer":"No.","docId":"130313pmt","qSentId":537,"aSentId":538}]